    <phenology>apr</phenology>
    <phenology>may</phenology>
    <habitat>gravelly soils of alkaline desert scrub and desert grasslands</habitat>
    <elevation>1200–1600 m;</elevation>
    <us_distribution>Ariz.</us_distribution>
    <discussion>Although endemic to northern Arizona, Pediocactus peeblesianus subsp. fickeiseniae
        is much more widespread than subsp. peeblesianus. “Pediocactus peeblesianus var.
        fickeiseniae L. D. Benson” was not validly published.</discussion>
